You can remove all duplicated elements from an array in JavaScript using various methods. Here's a simple program that utilizes a `Set` to achieve this:

```javascript
function removeDuplicates(arr) {
    // Use a Set to filter out duplicate elements
    const uniqueElements = new Set(arr);
    // Convert the Set back to an array
    return Array.from(uniqueElements);
}

const inputArray = [1, 2, 3, 2, 4, 3];
const result = removeDuplicates(inputArray);

console.log(result); // Output: [1, 2, 3, 4]
```

This program creates a new `Set` from the input array, which automatically removes any duplicates, and then converts it back to an array.

